{"ID":270266, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"266\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs265.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs267.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 266<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">Enoch was righteous enough to come into the presence of God, and walk with him,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> he must have\n  become so by keeping his commandments,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> and so of every righteous person,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> whether it was Noah,\n  a preacher of righteousness;<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> Abraham, the father of the faithful;<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> Jacob, the prevailer with God;<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span>\n  Moses, the man who wrote of Christ,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> and brought forth the law by commandment,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> as a\n  schoolmaster to bring men to Christ,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> or whether it was Jesus Christ himself, who had no need of\n  repentance,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> having no sin,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> according to his solemn declaration to John:&mdash;now let me be\n  baptized:<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> for no man can enter the kingdom without obeying this ordinance:<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> for thus it becometh\n  us to fulfil ALL RIGHTEOUSNESS.<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> Surely, then, if it became John and Jesus Christ, the Savior,\n  to fulfil all righteousness to be baptized&mdash;so surely, then, it will become every other person that\n  seeks the kingdom of heaven to go and do likewise;<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> for he is the door, and if any person climbs up\n  any other way, the same is a thief and a robber!<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Baptism Required in All Ages<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">In the former ages of the world, before the Savior came in the flesh,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> &ldquo;the saints&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> were\n  baptized<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> in the name of Jesus Christ to come,<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> because there never was any other name whereby\n  men could be saved;<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> and after he came in the flesh and was crucified, then the saints were baptized\n  in the name of Jesus Christ,<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> crucified, risen from the dead<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> and ascended into heaven,<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> that they\n  might be buried in baptism like him,<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> and be raised in glory like him,<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> that as there was but one\n  Lord, one faith, one baptism,<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span> and one God and father of us all,<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span> even so there was but one door<span class=\"footRef\">29<\/span>\n  to the mansions of bliss.<span class=\"footRef\">30<\/span> Amen. (Sept. 1, 1842.) T&amp;S 3:902-905.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">&ldquo;FACTS ARE STUBBORN THINGS&rdquo;<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Greatness of the Jaredites and Nephites<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">From an extract from &ldquo;Stephen&rsquo;s Incidents of Travel in Central America,&rdquo; it will be seen that the\n  proof of the Nephites and Lamanites dwelling on this continent, according to the account in the\n  Book of Mormon, is developing itself in a more satisfactory way than the most sanguine believer\n  in that revelation could have anticipated. It certainly affords us a gratification that the world of\n  mankind does not enjoy, to give publicity<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116946\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116946)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116946)\">Moses 7:69<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <s